SOM firmware is the firmware which runs on the EIC7X SoC of the SOM board.
The firmware includes ddr_fw.bin,sys_init.bin and bootloader.bin.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.ddr_fw.bin: DDR trainning and initialization firmware.
*Notes:
  The ddr_fw.bin is now able to cover 16GB and 32GB size of DDR.
  The ddr16G_init.bin and ddr32G_init.bin is deprecated.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.sys_init.bin: Board initialization, like PLL initialization and fan startup.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.bootloader.bin: It consists of OpenSBI and U-boot.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Notes:
nsign_bootloader_secboot_ddr_dvb2.bin is the bootchain file gengerated by
the nsign tool after packing sys_init.bin, ddr_fw.bin and bootloader.bin.

Users can generate your own bootchain with ddr_init.bin, sys_init.bin and
your own bootloader.bin by the nsign tool.

The DDR firmware of different frequency with ecc enabled is also provided, as
listed below:
e6611f2896895a88fd5f27d3d1b81fdc  ddr_fw_1600_ecc.bin
aa405f4199447c1aeaed1094b3e7b629  ddr_fw_3200_ecc.bin
f2f00b3d371fcd47d58184cfc998d331  ddr_fw_4266_ecc.bin
27f8aea0bd4379d0540d209d38327c2d  ddr_fw_5500_ecc.bin
e9af77fece23ba386824eb9d92ee354a  ddr_fw_6400_ecc.bin
When DDR ecc is enabled, 1/8 of the original DDR size starting from the highest
address is reserved for ecc space. Make sure this area is procted by pmp in
opensbi or the CPU speculative access mode is off, and is not used in uboot and
linux.

